- "Detailed performance statistics" refers to an extensive list of metrics, including total at-bats, runs, hits, RBIs, walks, strikeouts, left on base, innings pitched, earned runs, home runs allowed, hit by pitches, putouts, assists, errors, and double plays; 
- "Injury information" includes the type of injury, start and end dates, severity, recovery plan, and the physician in charge;
- The query specifically focuses on the 2023 season.

This query assumes a standard understanding of baseball statistics; 
A cumulative statistic refers to the sum of a player's performance metrics over multiple seasons; 
Average statistics are calculated by dividing the total sum of a metric by the number of seasons played;
The scouting report provides a qualitative assessment of the player's abilities and potential.
